        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/71c47a/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-05-07T19:19:29.027Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I’d like to request a small but meaningful improvement to the call interface on Android. Currently, accepting an incoming Signal call requires tapping a button. In contrast, the native phone app (and many other messaging apps) use a <em>swipe to accept</em> gesture, which feels much more natural and reliable—especially when pulling the phone out of a pocket or trying to answer quickly.</p>\n<p>For some reason, accepting Signal calls just feels clunkier compared to regular phone calls, and I believe replacing the tap-to-accept gesture with a swipe (or at least offering it as an option) would significantly improve the user experience.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 3,
        "updated_at": "2025-05-07T20:12:59.673Z",
